rComments: Don't take anything with her. She's unclear, unorganized, does things halfway... Basically the laziest accounting prof you can ever have. You're better off going to another lecture of just reading the textbook alone. She'll make you double guess yourself with her backwards teaching.

no. don't take this course if she is the only prof teaching it, even if it means it messed everything up, DON'T DO IT. she tries to be funny and realizes that not everyone likes this class, so its nice. She is usually late. She can be very abrupt and aggressive, it makes you not want to talk to her if you need help.

Her exams are so dumb, you can get marks for repeating yourself twice. No solutions for the cases so you have nothing to follow for the whole course except the BS and nonsense that comes out of her mouth. Take the CPA prep module if you can because I didn't learn a single thing about auditing.
Not helpful at all. In our experience, she didn't teach us a topic because she said it wouldn't be on the exam BUT it was.
Tries to be funny but isn't, not clear about what she is teaching, scribbles on the board without much explanation and is very messy.
